This paper is likely to belong to the numerical analysis (cs.NA) sub-category as it proposes a technique to accelerate local-global solvers for geometry optimization and physics simulation. It may also belong to the computer graphics (cs.CG) sub-category as physics simulation is often used in computer graphics applications. Additionally, it could be classified under the modeling and simulation (cs.MS) sub-category as it deals with simulation techniques. The paper may also fall under the control engineering (cs.SY) sub-category as it proposes a modification to improve stability. Finally, it could be classified under the computational engineering (cs.CE) sub-category as it deals with solving engineering problems using computational techniques.
